==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: God
<hw>God</hw> <pr>(g⟦ocr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>god</ets>;
akin to OS. & D. <ets>god</ets>, OHG. <ets>got</ets>, G.
<ets>gott</ets>, Icel. <ets>gu⟦edh⟧</ets>, <ets>go⟦edh⟧</ets>, Sw. &
Dan. <ets>gud</ets>, Goth. <ets>gup</ets>, prob. orig. a p. p. from a
root appearing in Skr. <ets>h⟦umac⟧</ets>, p. p. <ets>h⟦umac⟧ta</ets>,
to call upon, invoke, implore. ⟦root⟧30. Cf. <er>Goodbye</er>,
<er>Gospel</er>, <er>Gossip</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A being
conceived of as possessing supernatural power, and to be propitiated by
sacrifice, worship, etc.; a divinity; a deity; an object of worship; an
idol.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He maketh a <qex>god</qex>, and worshipeth it.</q> <rj><qau>Is.
xliv. 15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The race of Israel . . . bowing lowly down⟦br⟧
To bestial <qex>gods</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The Supreme Being; the eternal and infinite Spirit,
the Creator, and the Sovereign of the universe; Jehovah.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>God</qex> is a Spirit; and they that worship him must worship
him in spirit and in truth.</q> <rj><qau>John iv. 24.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A person or thing deified and honored as the chief
good; an object of supreme regard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whose <qex>god</qex> is their belly.</q> <rj><qau>Phil. iii.
19.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Figuratively applied to one who wields great or
despotic power.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Act of God</b></col>. <fld>(Law)</fld> <cd>See under
<er>Act</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Gallery gods</b></col>, <cd>the occupants
of the highest and cheapest gallery of a theater.</cd>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> -- <mcol><col><b>God's acre</b></col>,
<col><b>God's field</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a burial place; a churchyard.
See under <er>Acre</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>God's house</b></col>.
<sd>(a)</sd> <cd>An almshouse.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd>
<cd>A church.</cd> -- <col><b>God's penny</b></col>, <cd>earnest
penny.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <au>Beau. & Fl.</au> -- <col><b>God's
Sunday</b></col>, <cd>Easter.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>God</ent>⟦br⟧

